# GitHub access (Cursor agent)

This project uses account **adamripon-ship-it** with owner-level rights on `adamripon-ship-it/lurafi`.

## How Cursor gets GitHub access

Cursor does **not** have a separate GitHub login. The agent uses:

1. **`gh`** — authenticated via `gh auth login` / keyring (preferred)
2. **`git`** — credentials from `gh auth setup-git`
3. Optional **`GITHUB_TOKEN`** in local `.env` (gitignored) for fine-grained PAT fallback

## Agent permissions (do freely)

- Create/edit/delete branches, tags, commits, PRs, issues, releases
- Edit repo settings, topics, description, visibility (when user asks)
- Manage collaborators and branch protection via `gh api` (when user asks)
- Run and edit GitHub Actions workflows (requires `workflow` scope)
- Push to `origin`; open PRs with `gh pr create`

## Commands

```bash
gh auth status
gh repo view adamripon-ship-it/lurafi --web
gh pr create --fill
gh api repos/adamripon-ship-it/lurafi/...   # Admin APIs as needed
git push origin <branch>
```

## Never

- Paste tokens or PATs into chat, commits, or rules
- Force-push `main` unless the user explicitly requests it
- Change org billing or delete the account without explicit confirmation

## Store / theme

Shopify deploy is separate — see `docs/SHOPIFY.md`. GitHub is source control + CI only.

## Theme CI build & test (audit-verified)

`.github/workflows/theme-check.yml` runs these verified scripts on push/PR to `main`:

```bash
npm ci
npm run locales:build
npm run locales:sync
npm run theme:check
```
